ClientResponses.Response: It's really sad to hear how unhappy you are with the changes we've made but thank you for taking the time & letting us know.

Results.ReviewText: I have been drinking Gold Blend for over 40 years. It was my little taste of luxury in my student room and I have drunk it ever since. This new version does not taste anywhere near as good, it is bitter and leaves debris at the bottom of the cup. I know the debris is coffee grounds, but this is supposed to be instant coffee, and I don't expect to have a sticky mess at the bottom of the cup. Looks like I will now have to look elsewhere to buy my coffee.
Results.Title: Oh Dear, What have you done to Gold Blend

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for getting in touch. It saddens us to hear how much you don't like the new recipe for NESCAFÉ Gold Blend but we're listening to all consumer feedback. You could try NESCAFÉ Crema, this is a smoother alternative & doesn't contain the micro ground coffee that's been added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend. Find out more here: https://www.nescafe.co.uk/products/gold/nescaf%C3%A9-gold-crema-instant-coffee/

Results.ReviewText: Nescafe - given all the complaints and the sadness you feel about all of the feedback - what exactly are you going to do to put it right?  The new blend taste cheap, weak and tasteless.  I dont mind paying above the average price for decent coffee (as in the old formula)  and have been buying this for the last 25 years, but totally refuse to buy another jar of this when the cheaper stores own brand tastes better than this! Please change it back......
Results.Title: Cheap and Nasty - New Formula

ClientResponses.Response: Thank you very much for getting in touch & leaving your feedback about the recent changes we've made to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend. We'll certainly be making a note of your comments & circulating them to the rest of the team! The residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee!

Results.ReviewText: I have enjoyed Gold Blend for years. It has been my hug in a mug every morning. I am disabled. However, despite your commitment to "inclusive packaging" you have changed the shape of the jar, so it is now almost impossible for me to open. The coffee itself also tastes different and now has that horrible dark stuff ( like ground coffee) as you get near the end of your mug.
Results.Title: Awful

Results.ReviewText: I was weaned on coffee. I've thoroughly enjoyed it for decades and Nescafe is always at the top of my grocery list every week. I can't  imagine what I would do if I was denied the flavour of my favourite beverage first thing in the morning, it gives me the boost I need to start the day. For as long as I can remember I have enjoyed coffee and the changes have been brilliant in the way it is presented to the public in its various different flavours and choices available to suit every taste.  Nothing has changed my habits regarding coffee, I enjoy the same great taste and hopefully, will for many more years to come.
Results.Title: The taste keeps improving.

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thank you for sharing your feedback with us. We've added micro ground coffee to our NESCAFÉ Gold Blend to give it a richer aroma whilst maintaining the same smoothness. It saddens us to hear you don't like the changes we've made. Your comments have been noted to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: Why would you change a classic recipe? It's like the New Coke fiasco! I don't want to have grainy sludge at the bottom of my cup! Gold Blend is the coffee brand I have been drinking since a child. It's part of my life. A day hasn't gone by without it. And now it's ruined. If I wanted coffee beans, I'd buy coffee beans! I want instant! Pure, instant!
Results.Title: What a joke

Results.ReviewText: As hardened Gold Blend coffee drinkers of many years, we are very disappointed with the change. We loved the old recipe and didn't appreciate that the coffee had been altered before we purchased it - the label had changed but I didn't check the wording. True the insoluble solids have given the coffee a deep flavour but unfortunately for those of us who get headaches with coffee made from ground coffee beans the change makes it a non starter for us as the new coffee is having the same effect. Regretably I have a stock of the new recipe and will need to try a different brand now.
Results.Title: Hate the new recipe

Results.ReviewText: After many, many years of buying Gold Blend, this autumn I decided to try Aldi's Gold coffee. It strikes me as superior to Gold Blend, and is massively cheaper. I am, therefore, now a former consumer of Gold Blend.
Results.Title: I've switched to Aldi

Results.ReviewText: Have always been a gold blend drinker and can even remember many years ago collecting the gold beans of the jars of coffee purchased.If visiting family or friends if they dont have gold blend I opt to have tea because nothing tastes as good as gold blend.Now its been improved the taste is even richer smoother and once drank looking forward to my next cup.To be certain I never run out or my supermarket has no stock available I usually keep 4 or 5 200g jars in the cupboard because I would not drink any other brand ever.Also love the new shape of the jar bringing it up to the modern times will live in
Results.Title: new gold blend

ClientResponses.Response: It really saddens us to hear you're unhappy with the changes we've made but we really value your feedback. Thanks for getting in touch! Why don’t you try NESCAFÉ Crema, which has taste similar to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend, however is smoother, and does not contain micro ground coffee. Take a look here: https://goo.gl/a5GGWy

Results.ReviewText:
I have drunk Gold Blend for many years and have never found a better tasting instant coffee. I love the mild but rich flavour and the first cup in the morning was always worth getting up for. It has always been relatively expensive but I felt worth paying the extra. Unfortunately, now the taste and flavour is thin, cheap and bitter, and I dislike the sediment in the bottom of the cup.
I will  be searching for an alternative. Surely someone makes a coffee that is closer to how Gold Blend used to be.
Results.Title: Dear oh dear

Results.ReviewText: Sorry Nescafe but what have you done to this coffee, I have been buying it for years and it has changed. not for the better, please go back to the old blend it was much, much nicer. this leaves a residue in the cup and a nasty taste in the mouth,
Results.Title: aftertaste

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks very much for taking the time to come & leave your feedback regarding the new recipe. We're making a note of all comments & passing them to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: I have also been drinking Gold Blend for years, and enjoying it. Now you have changed the recipe I have been forced to find another brand. This residue in the cup is not what I want, if I did I would be drinking filter coffee. The main reason I drink instant is because of it's smooth flavour, without the coffee grinds.
Results.Title: Save Barista for another product.

ClientResponses.Response: It's disappointing to hear you're not a fan of the changes made. We really appreciate your feedback and have passed your thoughts to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText:
Almost as a warning of what was to come, the new shape of jar was less easy to hold and handle. The aroma on opening was different, but sadly not pleasant. The flavour on drinking is bitter by comparison to the old blend. The residue in the cup is unpalatable and an unwelcome accompaniment to a cup of instant coffee.
With this change in a well established product, you will lose customers including me.
Results.Title: Bad change

ClientResponses.Response: Hey *FNAME*, thank you for getting in touch with us. That's roast and ground coffee *FNAME*! It's nothing to be alarmed about and its actually a sign of quality coffee. After testing many recipes with our consumers, this recipe was the one they loved the most. We're really disappointed to hear you are not enjoying it, however we have added roast and ground coffee ground 10 times finer to give it a more intense aroma whilst maintaining the same smoothness. We are passing all comments onto the team and want to thank you again for the comment.

Results.ReviewText:
Why has my coffee changed ??? It doesn't taste the same it doesn't smell the same and I now get a nasty residue in the cup ! I can tried complaining directly to Nestle but the format will not accept best before end date so the email will not go. What can we do to get our coffee back ?
After 30 years of drinking Gold Blend I will now be looking for another suitable brand to kick start my day.
Results.Title: Recipe change

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for letting us know your thoughts on the new recipe. We really appreciate your feedback! The residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee! We've made a note of all your feedback & will be letting the rest of the team know!

Results.ReviewText: I have drunk Nescafe Gold Blend for 40 years and drunk no other coffee.  I drink it black – no milk, no sugar – so the taste is very important to me.  I do not drink coffee in coffee shops when out shopping – preferring to wait until I get back home to enjoy my own favourite cup.  I have taken it on holiday with me and to friends’ houses when staying overnight just so I can enjoy my wonderful cup of coffee first thing each morning.  I loved the rich aroma whenever I opened each new jar and looked forward to every cup I drank.  Your new version has no aroma on opening, a thin bitter taste and it leaves a dark sediment at the bottom of each cup.  What have you done!!?   Unfortunately, due to the fact that it was on offer at my local supermarket, I bought six jars.  It depresses me so much that I will have to suffer drinking this over the next coming months.  You have lost a very loyal customer.
Results.Title: Why oh why have you changed Gold Blend

Results.ReviewText: I recently purchased Nescafe Gold Blend coffee and was very pleased with the taste and overall quality. I liked the rich, bold tones of the coffee and how it tasted like a true barista - made beverage. So easy to make, I just added boiled water that had slightly cooled. Perfect on it's own, as my husband likes it, or with cream, as I prefer. A really refreshing way to start the day. True coffee lovers will not be disappointed.
Results.Title: Great tasting coffee

Results.ReviewText: I have been using Gold Blend coffee for at least 20 years and I was excited to see the new jar and contents.  Unfortunately, I find since starting to use the new jar and blend there appears to be a problem  -  the coffee does not seem to dissolve fully and one is left with a sediment at the bottom of the cup.  I have asked several friends who also use Gold Blend if they had experienced the same problem and they confirmed that they had also noted the sediment.  I must say that the taste is still perfect but the above noted problem renders the overall experience a little disappointing.  I would now give overall rating of 3 stars where as before I would have give overall rating 5 stars.
Results.Title: Disappointed

ClientResponses.Response: It's really disappointing to hear this but thank you very much for taking the time & letting us know your thoughts on the changes we've made.

Results.ReviewText: Thought at first I had bought a jar from sub standard batch but see from the recent reviews blend has changed. Nasty gritty dregs and unpleasant aftertaste. After many years of rating gold blend 5 star will now be looking for a new brand

Results.ReviewText:
The very first action I take on waking is to make a cup of coffee and it has to be Gold Blend for me even removing the lid is a pleasure as there is always a delicious aroma that rises from the jar. I have tasted other brands but always return to my favourite Nescafe coffee.
I find the refill packs extremely useful as they are less weight than the jars and this is so much easier to carry and they are also ecofriendly.
Results.Title: Blissful wakeup

Results.Title: Beautifully Smooth

ClientResponses.Response: Thank you very much for getting in touch & letting us know! Your comments will be noted & passed to the rest of the team!

Results.ReviewText: Very disappointing in flavour and quality. I do not like the residue left at the end of the drink, it is coarse and bitter. I also had to advise a friend who can only drink Instanf Coffee (medical reasons eg Ulcerative Colitis) that there is residue left at the end, and this is one reason she cannot drink Fresh/Filter Coffee. A VERY IMPORTANT FACTOR.
Results.Title: NESCAFE GOLD BLEND Instant Coffee

Results.ReviewText:
I bought a jar of Nescafe Gold Rich and Smooth recently and found it to be much nicer than the previous Nescafe Gold product.  The new jar and 'come and buy 
 me' packaging is eye-catching, while the coffee oozes quality from the moment you pick up the jar and open it to let a delicious aroma escape and make that first cup.  The coffee itself is not a disappointment, offering a smooth, rich taste and value for money.  Depending on your own likes or dislikes, try it with Baileys and thick cream squirted on top for a sophisticated after dinner cup of coffee, or add a tot of Brandy to a black coffee.
Results.Title: Rich Experience

Results.ReviewText: Having been a coffee drinker for the best part of 30 years Nescafé is always My go to brand. I have tried several of the Nescafé blends but gold blend is my favourite. It's a smooth, aromatic all round great tasting coffee it never fails to satisfy me. It's great on its own as a dark rich coffee or with a splash of milk for that curl up comfort coffee either way you'll not be disappointed with gold blend in my opinion it's one of nescafe's finest and wholly recommend it to anyone that listens/reads... Happy drinking :)
Results.Title: Coffee at its best

Results.ReviewText: I only drink black coffee, and have done for approx 50 years, and Gold Blend has been my #1 choice as along as I can remember..... The new mix is no longer a premium coffee, the aroma has gone, its weaker, and it leaves a gritty after-taste. Very disappointing.......and now very average.
Results.Title: What have to done!!

Results.ReviewText: After years of drinking coffee I had somehow been stuck in the cycle of buying supermarket own-brand. I actually believed it tasted just as good as branded products! I tried Nescafe Gold yesterday as a sample in Tescos and immediately had to purchase some (I am actually tempted to go back to the store now and stock up so that I don't run out). Usually I drink coffee just to keep me ticking over throughout the day, however, this is so delicious that I find my self savoring every cup. I enjoyed it so much that I had a cup at 23.40 last night! (naughty I know - and i definitely paid for it). This is a product that will replace my routine stops to coffee shops, thank-you for saving me a fortune.
Results.Title: I forgot how good coffee could taste!

ClientResponses.Response: It's sad to hear this, but thank you very much for sharing your feedback with us.

Results.ReviewText: Tried this new coffee and it is not so good as old type complete different taste and did not like
Results.Title: Take back

Results.ReviewText:
My husband and I love the taste of this aromatic and delicious coffee. We first tried Gold Blend in a refill pack that was on special offer in our local supermarket. We have bought Nescafe Gold Blend ever since. 
You can taste the quality and strong aromatic flavour in every mug full of this coffee, and by buying the refill packs, our coffee jar is never empty.  
Buying the refill packs I find is both cost effective and kind to the environment.
I think personally that Gold Blend is good value for money and worth trying. You will not be disappointed :D
Results.Title: The Coffee for Us!

Results.ReviewText:
I first bought Nescafe Gold Blend via an in-store promotional half price offer a few weeks ago.
After using the product for a few times I am happy to say that I would not have been dissapointed if I had paid full price for this wonderful coffee.
It is full bodied and smooth, with a rich full flavour. 
I have drunk this coffee black and unsweetened (my personal preference) but also tried it with milk and cream. Whichever way it is drunk. The flavour stays rich and smooth with absolutely no trace of any bitter aftertaste often found in similar coffees offered by other so called premium brands. I suggest that you try it for yourself if you have not already done so and I promise you won't be dissapointed.
Results.Title: Smooth As Silk

Results.ReviewText:
I have been drinking this coffee for years now and have managed to buy it in Australia, Japan and Greece where I have been living as well as in the UK.  My husband and I really enjoy this coffee and love the taste as we both drink black coffee.  When I saw that you had created 4 new blends I was worried, but our regular choice tastes just the same but a bit richer which is a good point.  
I did notice though that I have a slight sediment at the bottom of an empty mug – similar to using real coffee, but no complaints.  However, the 300g refill is now 275g in weight and the price has gone up!
Results.Title: Love this coffee - great taste, reliable

Well you have messed up good style as far as I am concerned because I can No longer drink it to the dregs because you get grinds in the bottom of the the cup and this makes me sick you have totally messed up.  If I wanted to have filtered coffee I would buy filtered coffee so please change the blend back to it's original blend I want to enjoy my drink again.  The original blend was perfection so why spoil  it
